The article provides a summary of a teleconference call held by senior administration officials to discuss the second Summit for Democracy. The call was on background and embargoed until the end of the call. The officials discussed the summit's focus on advancing technology for democracy and combating the misuse of technology. They highlighted several initiatives, including a presidential initiative for democratic renewal with $690 million in new funding, the Republic of Korea's offer to host a third summit, and efforts to counter the proliferation and misuse of commercial spyware. The officials also mentioned the release of a governmental declaration from the summit, which had endorsements from 73 countries, and addressed questions about the number of countries that declined the invitation to attend the summit.